      "content": "it's interesting how you framed it that way. so basically, if i'm writing my debate brief, you're saying the humanitarian side is the \"correct\" moral stance and the border security side is just a secondary, more practical concern rather than a real moral argument? is it fair to say that prioritizing borders is inherently less ethical than prioritizing human rights?",
